      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening; contact modeled with penalty formulation; geometric nonlinearity enabled. Model form justified by prior literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "An elastoplastic material model with isotropic hardening was selected for the Ti-6Al-4V screw and UHMWPE block components, consistent with published material characterization data. Geometric nonlinearity was enabled to capture large-displacement behavior. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) was applied at screw-block interfaces. Model form uncertainty was quantified via sensitivity analysis and found to be within acceptable bounds."
