    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA ensemble demonstrates sufficient credibility for the stated COU. All 13 V&V 40 factors were assessed; 12 of 13 factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration and the regulatory decision does not require multi-condition validation at this stage. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria. Package is submitted under ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and will be appended prior to final archival submission.",
